</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="27" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
Family 
<taxonomicName authority="Hirayama, 1988" authorityName="Hirayama" authorityYear="1988" family="Priscomilitaridae" higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" rank="family">Priscomilitaridae Hirayama, 1988</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="27" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
This family name was subsequently used as 
<taxonomicName above-genus="Priscomilitariidae" family="Priscomilitariidae" lsidName="" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" rank="above-genus">Priscomilitariidae</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Myers, AA" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Crustacean Biology" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" pagination="443 - 485" title="A phylogeny and a new classification of the Corophiidea Leach, 1814 (Amphipoda)." url="10.1651/0278-0372(2003)023[0443:APAANC]2.0.CO;2" volume="23" year="2003">Myers and Lowry (2003)</bibRefCitation>
. The generic name of its type species, 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Priscomilitaridae" genus="Priscomilitaris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Priscomilitaris" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Priscomilitaris</taxonomicName>
, ends in a Latin word, militaris (genitive militaris, stem militar-). Therefore, the stem of this family name should be Priscomilitar- according to the Art 29.3. of the Code (
<bibRefCitation author="Hou, Z" journalOrPublisher="The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" title="International Code of Zoological Nomenclature" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
). The original spelling by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hirayama, A" journalOrPublisher="Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" pagination="39 - 77" title="Taxonomic studies on the shallow water gammaridean Amphipoda of west Kyushu, Japan. VIII. Pleustidae, Podoceridae, Priscomilitaridae, Stenothoidae, Synopiidae, and Urothoidae." volume="33" year="1988">Hirayama (1988)</bibRefCitation>
is thus obviously correct. Because 
<bibRefCitation author="Myers, AA" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Crustacean Biology" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" pagination="443 - 485" title="A phylogeny and a new classification of the Corophiidea Leach, 1814 (Amphipoda)." url="10.1651/0278-0372(2003)023[0443:APAANC]2.0.CO;2" volume="23" year="2003">Myers and Lowry (2003)</bibRefCitation>
did not provide a statement for any demonstrably intentional change of the spelling 
<taxonomicName family="Priscomilitaridae" lsidName="" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" rank="family">Priscomilitaridae</taxonomicName>
, the spelling 
<taxonomicName above-genus="Priscomilitariidae" family="Priscomilitariidae" lsidName="" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" rank="above-genus">Priscomilitariidae</taxonomicName>
is an incorrect subsequent spelling according to the Art 33.3. of the Code. This incorrect spelling is used in the influential web sources, e.g. WoRMS (
<bibRefCitation author="Horton, T" editor="Horton, T" journalOrPublisher="Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" title="World Amphipoda Database: accessed through World Register of Marine Species" url="http://www.marinespecies.org/aphia.php?p=taxdetails&amp;id=550580" year="2015">Horton and Lowry 2015</bibRefCitation>
). The incorrect spelling of 
<taxonomicName family="Priscomilitaridae" lsidName="" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" rank="family">Priscomilitaridae</taxonomicName>
on those web registries should be emended to avoid additional erroneous citations of the spelling of this family name.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
